The paper discusses image processing methodologies and non-rigid pixel-wise registration, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and image processing (cs.IM). The paper also mentions the use of objective quality measures, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM). The methodology proposed in the paper involves dealing with complex multiscale motion during the acquisition process, which requires techniques from information theory (cs.IT) and numerical analysis (cs.NA).
